Package application

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ChangePasswordController
    This class allows the user to change their password and update their details in the employees database.
    Employee
    This class represents and employee and holds data about them.
    EmployeeOrder
    This class stores only the relevant information needed from the order class.
    Item
    This class defines items in the menu.
    LoginController
    This class allows the user to login to their account and takes them to the manager main page if they are a amanager, or a waiter main page otherwise.
    Main
    This is the starting class which initiates the welcome page.
    ManagerMainController
    This class allows the user to navigate to all the pages available to the manager.
    MenuController
    This class allows the manager to edit, add or delete menu items and then saves these items to the menu file.
    Order
    This class stores the details of every new order.
    OrderController
    This class creates a new order object as long as there are ordered items.
    OrderItem
    This class holds information about the individual items in an order.
    OrderListController
    This class displays a list of searched orders in separate tables and allows only managers to export them to files.
    OrderTableController
    This class produces a list of existing orders for managers to view employee activities.
    SearchController
    This class allows the user to search orders according to their number, their table number, their price or the time of order.
    TableViewController
    The Class TableViewController.
    WaiterListController
    This class displays the employees in the restaurant and allows managers to edit, add or delete employees.
    WaiterMainController
    This class allows the user to navigate to any of the pages available to waiters.
    WelcomePageController
    The main page of the restaurant management system.
